name: Spice Goa

reviews.review_text: In a quest to search for the best Goan fish thali, we landed here on a weekend during lunch hours and oh boy, it was a painful wait of an hour in the scorching heat. Even after we had booked a table for 8 the previous night through Easy Diner platform, the restaurant denied and did not honour our booking because of an issue between them and the Easy Diner platform. We were seated on the top deck after an hour and we ordered a few Fish Thalis, King Fish masala fry, egg fried rice, chicken lollipops, Goan veg platter and veg biryani and a few drinks to go with it. As soon as the thali arrived, we started belting and collectively decided that this was the best Goan Fish thali out of all the thalis we had during our 6-day trip to Goa. The prawns curry, the boneless fish fry, the sides to go with it were all very tasty and fulfilling. Even the barfi on the plate was too good. Chicken lollipops and egg fried rice were great too. King Fish masala fry was a bit sour to our taste and was not liked by everyone. The server did give us a heads up about it before we ordered it, so it's all good. The only disappointment was the Goan veg platter. Paying a premium for such less veg sides was not a good plan and the items did not taste very well either. Overall, it was a great experience devouring Goan fish thali and other seafood and chicken items here. A worthy visit and I highly recommend this place for other tourists/travellers. The restrooms were neat and clean and the sinks were kept well and tidy too. The restaurant has won a lot of awards and accolades and the same has been stuck on the wall and one can witness it while going to the top deck. The only nitpicking here i would do is the cramped space and how tiny the restaurant and the waiting area is. It is a very cramped space and a 6 feet human has to bend and watch their head on the top deck while walking around. Even the crowd gets too busy and takes away the ambience of having good food. The waiting area is overfilled during peak lunch hours and one has to stay back in the heat while their family and/or friends wait in the car with the comfort of air conditioning until they get a table confirmation.

Great food, Service and atmosphere is good too.
You can try goan food and north Indian as well.

Overhyped restaurant. The cramped & noisy ambience is a telltale of the obnoxious & rude service being provided by the outlet. We found no tissues on the table,no water was offered,no finger bowls & a general apathy towards customers. The food at best was decent. Nothing to match the hype. Plenty of brilliant restaurants in Goa. Makes no sense visiting this restaurant. Not recommended.

description:
**Spice Goa: A Culinary Journey in Tivim**

Nestled in the vibrant locale of Tivim, Spice Goa boasts an inviting overall rating of **4.4**, supported by an impressive **5,300 reviews**. This beloved establishment is particularly known for its delightful **Goan cuisine**, with standout offerings like the **fish thali**, earning consistent praise (361 mentions), along with hints of traditional treats like **serradura** (68 mentions) and the unique dining experience on a **banana leaf** (55 mentions). With such resounding accolades, one might expect a transcendent dining experience, but some reviews hint at undercurrents that travelers should consider.

**Ambiance & Design**

As you approach Spice Goa, the modest exterior may not hint at the culinary delights awaiting inside. Upon entering, diners are greeted by a somewhat **cramped and bustling space**, especially during peak times, as noted by several patrons. The top deck, where most guests are seated, provides a slightly elevated view, but the atmospheric elements can sometimes feel stifling due to the sheer volume of diners. The **lighting** is functional and bright, perhaps aiming to deliver a warm ambiance, yet the **noisy environment** can detract from the intimate experience many seek. The walls adorned with awards and accolades showcase the restaurant‚Äôs recognition; however, customers have reported elements like **missing tissues** and the occasional lack of service attentiveness that conflict with the prestige displayed.

![Spice Goa Dining Area](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/geougc-cs/AHRlGdkIcdRLu-7XEimwvX6a4PAnLhLgQHSzxG2aW5dp-fqCqVilvzd02b7iNNAdNj1LBc63vwpDNSi_3AHSpu1gWFJz26pauZryFb3FtYkimftycsNNOcQxAXdxfBuc7614qudE8aG6YA=w375-h281-p)

**Menu & Culinary Experience**

The culinary offerings at Spice Goa center around its celebrated **Goan fish thali**, which has garnered accolades as the best during a week's voyage through Goa. Reviewers sing praises for the **prawns curry** and the **boneless fish fry** included in the thali, highlighting the experience of sampling multiple delightful flavors in one plate. The colorful presentation of each dish adds to the experience, with portions crafted to ensure diners leave feeling satisfied.

Aside from the fish thali, the menu features a range of options including **egg fried rice**, **chicken lollipops**, and a **vegetarian platter**. However, the vegetarian option has received mixed feedback, with some finding it underwhelming given the premium price. **Dietary options** are available for both Goan and North Indian cuisine, catering to a range of palates, and various refreshing **shakes and drinks** complement the dishes.

![Goan Fish Thali](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/geougc-cs/AHRlGdkkte5yXnrZAZ07jJH93GYSr1fOcpy1MWgfdi_NoHcpwt2WQYArI_94a_NLPWZY0uRiT-W0kxI0GrRYLxCfhRJ4WvAvaT8mGjazJcwkvGI3Sg_9hAvQIzUPBLihNdrKzdU7mDBR=w375-h281-p)

**Customer Experience & Service**

Customer experiences at Spice Goa oscillate between commendable and disappointing. Many reviewers appreciate the flavorful dishes and the **friendly service**, yet there are contrasting sentiments regarding wait times and space limitations. Frequent mentions of **overcrowding** and inefficient handling of reservations raise concerns, as highlighted in a particular review detailing a frustrating hour-long wait despite prior booking. While the cleanliness of facilities is a positive point noted by customers, repeated reports of neglect in service, such as not offering essential amenities, do tarnish the overall experience.

**Popularity & Reviews**

The buzz around Spice Goa is palpable, with a mix of enthusiastic accolades and critiques. Many consider it a must-visit for tourists seeking a genuine taste of Goan culture and cuisine, while others caution against the hype, suggesting that **quieter establishments** might offer a more pleasant dining experience. The restaurant‚Äôs numerous awards displayed within its walls proclaim its recognition, though reviews hint at a disconnect between popular opinion and actual experience for some diners.

![Kingfish Masala Fry](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/geougc-cs/AHRlGdlxelpnPdnbJWc2WgyW5a-RqFZIqoNrmqYnJtsTi6fku384m-SsLytPi23U7B-ItkBCypH89XRIq-Q1OsGCe0n6tUuBsWz3cH_ioW7H9eJcl8yhB2iEZdRgpEr-dhc6LawO2j9V=w375-h281-p)

**In Conclusion**

Spice Goa stands out with its reputation for authentic Goan flavors, particularly its acclaimed fish thali. While the food may resonate deeply with many patrons, the challenges faced regarding space and service efficiency suggest potential diners should proceed with tempered expectations. If you can navigate the bustling ambiance and are patient with potential wait times, Spice Goa might just reward you with a satisfying experience steeped in the rich culinary traditions of Goa.
